# Update llms-full, CLI help, and runtime comments for durable queue semantics and startup ordering

## Requirements

- Update docs and help text so they describe the real durable queue semantics rather than the old direct-history fallback.
- Document startup ordering relative to pending agent resume.
- Keep implementation, operator docs, and developer docs in sync.

## Acceptance Criteria

- `docs/public/llms-full.txt` and relevant CLI help text describe offline enqueue, startup replay, and at-least-once behavior accurately.
- Any runtime comments that explain startup ordering or queue semantics reflect the final implementation.
- There is no remaining user-facing documentation that implies offline inject writes immediately to chat history.
